13 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Subsection 2 of section 5-01-19.2 of the North Dakota Century
14 Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
15 2. A manufacturing distillery may sell spirits produced by that distillery at off sale, in retail
16 lots, and not for resale, and may sell or direct ship its spirits to persons inside or
17 outside the state in a manner consistent with the laws of the place of the sale or
18 delivery in total quantities not in excess of twenty-five thousandone hundred fifty
19 thousand gallons [94635567812 liters] in a calendar year.
20 a. Direct sales within this state are limited to two and thirty-eight hundredths gallons
21 [9 liters] or less per month per person for personal use and not for resale. The
22 packaging must conform with the labeling requirements in section 5-01-16. A
23 licensee may dispense free samples of the spirits offered for sale. Subject to local
24 ordinance, sales at off sale may be made on Sundays between twelve noon and
25 twelve midnight.
26 b. A manufacturing distillery may hold events inside its premises and at its satellite
27 location. The tax commissioner may issue event permits for not more than forty
28 event days per calendar year to a manufacturing distillery to allow the
29 manufacturing distillery, subject to local ordinance, to give free samples of its
30 product and to sell its product by the glass or in closed containers at on-premises
31 events on the premises, off the premises, and at its satellite location.
